mbor/yoaHjA_wOju5M3i5pFkCxSaldFg=/0x0:1000x1000/600x600/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 600w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NhWEaXktv6KC06Uoc1kE7klytkI=/0x0:1000x1000/700x700/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 700w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2fUgeFQnuC68v3-NlIP2YD-QDy4=/0x0:1000x1000/800x800/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 800w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fwgjrDROfhTZxXWJGdIgYrcOluI=/0x0:1000x1000/900x900/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 900w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/k-QthKsACWCWuRcT3EI8YXmF1gA=/0x0:1000x1000/1000x1000/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1000w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vMp3oBnSpe4jxKPmVq_B3I1-Yds=/0x0:1000x1000/1100x1100/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1100w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cXIQa0ZEOrcCKqRiAo-IspX6dZM=/0x0:1000x1000/1200x1200/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1200w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g2vzdCUnmY6AdmIHVnoqHeEhdpw=/0x0:1000x1000/1300x1300/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1300w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OQWBdPq3OCRRCEKzUIZdfWCd5qM=/0x0:1000x1000/1400x1400/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1400w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sf5P0c1T7d1Q-HsjfNHBFY_sRho=/0x0:1000x1000/1500x1500/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1500w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W81MTuvnX1VQeNK3c1W9EMsi75Q=/0x0:1000x1000/1600x1600/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ULw3T8HBl1oTgOjXDSiZ-QOOK6k=/0x0:1000x1000/1700x1700/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1700w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Yu41J3lr0sb66oWT8jB0gK1pzWE=/0x0:1000x1000/1800x1800/filters:focal(500x500:501x501)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23390220/ajohnson_220411_5138_0001_squ.jpg 1800w\" sizes=\"100vw\"></picture></a></p><h3>Motorola Moto G Stylus (2022)</h3><ul><li>$300</li></ul><p>The Moto G Stylus complements its namesake feature with good everyday performance and a big 1080p display, though it doesn’t include 5G connectivity.</p>', '2022-07-31 14:23:51', NULL);
INSERT INTO `news` (`id`, `type`, `title`, `image`, `intro`, `desc`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(7, 'Best Budgets', 'Top 10 Apple and Android smartphones you can buy for under $800', '1659277759.jpg', '<p>In 2020, it’s all too easy to spend too much money on a smartphone - especially if you’re only looking at the most popular brands</p><p>Apple’s top-end iPhone 12, iPhone 11 Pro and iPhone 12 Pro Max can cost you thousands, and Samsung’s own high-spec Galaxy S20 and Galaxy Note 20 Ultra aren’t that much cheaper.</p><p>Thankfully, these days it’s much easier to find a cheaper and more budget-friendly alternative to these flagship devices than ever before. The amount of overlap in features for mid-tier devices and premium ones continues to grow while the gap in quality continues to shrink. The mid-tier smartphone market has never felt so flagship.</p>', '<h2>Google Pixel 4a&nbsp;</h2><p><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/990x990/products/12980_8_screenshot_2020-09-14_479126-product-1-i-637317873068055522_1000x1000_jpg_webp_image_1000__1000_pixels.png\" alt=\"Google Pixel 4a\"></p><p><i>Credit: Google</i>Google Pixel 4a</p><p>The Google Pixel 4a doesn’t have anything particularly revolutionary inside it but, for the AU$599 asking price, it pretty much blows every other mid-ranger out of the water.</p><p>As with the previous Pixel 3a, the Pixel 4a nabs you the same slick, clean and expansive version of Android found in the flagship Pixel 4 plus a camera that’s almost just as good.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/671618/oppo-coming-apple-watch-their-own-premium-wearable/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/screenshot_2020-03-09_oppos_first_smartwatch_is_the_oddly_familiar_oppo_watch.png\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/671618/oppo-coming-apple-watch-their-own-premium-wearable/\">Oppo are coming for the Apple Watch with their own premium wearable</a></p><p>In our review, we came away impressed and said that “If you don’t want an iPhone and you’re on a budget, then the Pixel 4a is a tremendous option. For less than six hundred dollars you get a superlative camera, guaranteed three years of software support, all-day battery life, and clean Android software with exclusive features in a phone that you can hold in one hand. It’s surprising how rare that is to find today, let alone at such a good price.”</p><p><strong>You can read our full review </strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/review/google/pixel-4a/682878/\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p><h3>Pros:</h3><p>Incredible camera</p><p>Clean software</p><p>OLED screen</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/671132/why-doesn-t-telstra-offer-512gb-version-samsung-galaxy-s20-ultra-5g/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/galaxy-s20-ultra-bump-100831718-orig.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/671132/why-doesn-t-telstra-offer-512gb-version-samsung-galaxy-s20-ultra-5g/\">Why doesn\'t Telstra offer the 512GB version of the Samsung Galaxy S20 Ultra 5G?</a></p><h3>Cons:</h3><p>No wireless charging</p><p>No water resistance</p><p>Physical fingerprint sensor &amp; no Face Unlock</p><h3>Where to buy?</h3><p>In Australia, you can buy the Google Pixel 4a outright through the following retailers:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/685610/samsung-galaxy-s21-everything-need-know/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/galaxy-s21_ultra_lifestyle_black_spen.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/685610/samsung-galaxy-s21-everything-need-know/\">Samsung Galaxy S21: Everything You Need To Know</a></p><p><a href=\"https://store.google.com/au/product/pixel_4a\">Google</a> - AU$599</p><p><a href=\"https://www.jbhifi.com.au/products/google-pixel-4a-128gb-just-black\">JB Hi-Fi</a> - AU$599</p><p><a href=\"https://www.officeworks.com.au/shop/officeworks/p/google-pixel-4a-unlocked-smartphone-128gb-just-black-brga02099\">Officeworks</a> - AU$597</p><p><a href=\"https://www.harveynorman.com.au/google-pixel-4a-128gb-just-black.html\">Harvey Norman</a> - AU$599</p><p><a href=\"https://www.kogan.com/au/buy/google-pixel-4a-128gb-just-black-google/?utm_source=google&amp;utm_medium=product_listing_ads&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjw8MD7BRArEiwAGZsrBazAPhD7jSlUpb3GSrHvqWi6W9scKv_uVKKpvJndA3XyRvJquwBalhoCq4cQAvD_BwE\">Kogan</a> - AU$569</p><p>The Google Pixel 4a is also available on any postpaid mobile plans via Vodafone and Telstra. Check out the widget below for more.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/648496/samsung-unveil-galaxy-book-2/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/galaxy_book_2_sv_v_right_keyboard_up_spen_rgb-950x662.jpeg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/648496/samsung-unveil-galaxy-book-2/\">Samsung unveil Galaxy Book 2</a></p><h2>Oppo Reno4 Z 5G</h2><p><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/990x990/dimg/2up-oppo-reno4-z-5g-white-front45right-rgb.png\" alt=\"Oppo Reno4 Z 5G\"></p><p><i>Credit: Oppo</i>Oppo Reno4 Z 5G</p><p>A learner, cheaper companion to Oppo’s 5G-ready Reno4, the Reno4 Z 5G successfully replicates most of what makes the former one of the more compelling sub-$1000 devices out there.</p><p>Priced at thrifty AU$599, the Reno4 Z packs in 5G-connectivity, a 6.5-inch LCD screen clocked at 120Hz, 8GB of RAM, 128GB of storage plus a quad-lens rear camera. You won\'t find flagship perks like wireless charging, water-resistance or the Find series’ famed 10x lossless zoom but you will find an in-screen fingerprint sensor, a 4000mAh battery and a surprisingly-capable camera for the price point.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/review/sony/wf-sp900/649639/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/screenshot_2018-11-15_sony_wf-sp900_sports_wireless_headphones2.png\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/review/sony/wf-sp900/649639/\">Sony WF-SP900 review: One step forward, two steps back</a></p><h3>Pros</h3><p>Sleek design</p><p>In-display fingerprint sensor</p><p>Great performance</p><h3>Cons</h3><p>No wireless charging</p><p>No water resistance</p><p>ColorOS can be an acquired taste</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/686026/oppo-unveils-entry-level-a15-smartphone/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/oppo_a15.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/686026/oppo-unveils-entry-level-a15-smartphone/\">Oppo unveils entry level A15 smartphone</a></p><h3>Where to buy?</h3><p>In Australia, you can buy the Oppo Reno4 Z 5G outright at the following retailers:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.jbhifi.com.au/products/oppo-reno4-z-5g-128gb-dew-white\">JB Hi-Fi </a>- AU$599</p><p>Woolworths&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com.au/gp/product/B082LX322C/ref=as_li_qf_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=pcworldanz-22&amp;creative=1211&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;creativeASIN=B082LX322C&amp;linkId=72cf4c91b1b1a72eb2bbe4fe113f9cf8\">Amazon</a></p><p>Bing Lee</p><p><a href=\"https://www.mobileciti.com.au/oppo-reno-4-z-5g\">MobileCiti </a>- AU$59</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/648159/samsung-announces-availability-2nd-gen-frame-tv/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/samsung_the_frame_-_lifestyle_17.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/648159/samsung-announces-availability-2nd-gen-frame-tv/\">Samsung announces availability of 2nd Gen Frame TV</a></p><p>You can buy the Oppo Reno4 Z 5G on a post-paid plan through Woolworths Mobile:</p><h2>Samsung Galaxy A90</h2><p><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/990x990/dimg/screenshot_2020-09-28_samsung_galaxy_a90_5g_128gb_6gb_48mp_-_black_amazon_com_au_electronics.png\" alt=\"Samsung Galaxy A90\"></p><p><i>Credit: Samsung</i>Samsung Galaxy A90</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/647629/oppo-named-market-leader-sub-premium-smartphones-by-counterpoint/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/oppo0347_2.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/647629/oppo-named-market-leader-sub-premium-smartphones-by-counterpoint/\">OPPO named market leader for sub-premium smartphones by Counterpoint</a></p><p>Even if the waterproofing is a conspicuous omission, the Samsung Galaxy A90 still manages to hold up as an impressively adept mid-ranger that hits a surprising amount of the same notes as its flagship inspirations. Building on the legacy of the Galaxy A70, which our review praised as \"more than the smartphone you can get away with\", the Galaxy A90 is Samsung\'s first mid-tier phone with 5G connectivity.</p><p>The device is also equipped with a 6.7-inch Full HD+ Super AMOLED screen, Snapdragon 855 processor,&nbsp; a triple-lens camera (48-megapixel + 5-megapixel depth sensor + 8-megapixel wide-angle lens), 32-megapixel front-facing camera, 128GB of storage, up to 8GB of RAM, a 4500mAh battery and an in-screen fingerprint sensor.</p><h3>Pros</h3><p>Great performance</p><p>Quad-lens camera</p><p>In-display fingerprint sensor</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/650916/rise-superphone/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/screenshot_2018-10-20_iphone_xs_and_iphone_xs_max_bring_the_best_and_biggest_displays_to_iphone_3.png\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/650916/rise-superphone/\">The Rise Of The Superphone</a></p><h3>Cons</h3><p>No wireless charging</p><p>No water resistance</p><h3>Where to buy</h3><p>In Australia, you can buy the Samsung Galaxy A90 outright at the following retailers:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/651062/lg-five-camera-v40-thinq-will-come-australia-february/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/screenshot_2018-12-20_v40_thinq_blue_on_shot_03_-_co