</i>Oppo Find X2 Lite</p><p>Oppo\'s Find X2 Lite sits right on the line between their formal flagships and the more affordable Reno series. It\'s got a lot of the same hardware guts as the Find X2 Neo and Find X2 Pro but lacks some of the thrills.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/review/oppo/find-x2-lite/681501/\">In our review of the Oppo Find X2 Lite, </a>we said that \"Though imperfect on its own, there are going to be people out there for whom the Oppo Find X2 Lite is a perfect fit. It doesn’t indulge in the decadent design or flagship thrills of its pricier counterparts but delivers more than what you’d expect when it comes to everyday utility, camera quality and battery life.\"<br>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>You can read our full review </strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/review/oppo/find-x2-lite/681501/\"><strong>here</strong></a><strong>.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/685608/does-samsung-galaxy-s21-microsd-slot/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/galaxy-s21_plus_violet_silver_black.jpg\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/685608/does-samsung-galaxy-s21-microsd-slot/\">Does the Samsung Galaxy S21 have a MicroSD slot?</a></p><h3>Pros</h3><p>5G-capable Snapdragon processor<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Great battery life<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Headphone jack<br>&nbsp;</p><h3>Cons</h3><p>No telephoto lens, so no less zoom<br>&nbsp;</p><p>No water resistance&nbsp;</p><p>No wireless charging</p><p><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/687751/nokia-g10-mid-range-phone-large-battery-lands-australia/\"><img src=\"https://www.idgcdn.com.au/dimg/120x120/dimg/nokia_g10_dusk_main.png\"></a> <strong>READ MORE</strong><a href=\"https://www.pcworld.idg.com.au/article/687751/nokia-g10-mid-range-phone-large-battery-lands-australia/\">The Nokia G10, a mid-range phone with a large battery, lands in Australia</a></p><h3>Where to buy?</h3><p>In Australia, you can 